    public abstract class Racer
extends RenderableObject

    Racer

    Abstract class which represents all karts driving around on the map

    This class handles the bulk of things that define a Racer (someone in a kart) in the game world. This includes primarily things related to how a Racer moves around the game world, as well as how they interact with Items and each other. Doesn't define any static methods, but does have an abstract method for the Enemy and Player subclasses to implement.
    Author:
    Daniel Porteous porteousd 696965

    • Constructor Detail

      • Racer

        public Racer(double startX,
             double startY)
      throws org.newdawn.slick.SlickException
        As well as calling the super constructor, which mainly just places the object on the map, this constructor sets the values relating to the movement of the Racer to the standard constants. An ArrayList of Items is also created and given an initial size of 3, a size which likely wouldn't need to be increase considering that it's almost impossible for a Racer to be under more than 3 active effects at one time.
        Parameters:
        startX - In pixels. Horizontal x-coordinate starting position.
        startY - In pixels. Vertical y-coordinate starting position.
        Throws:
        org.newdawn.slick.SlickException

    • Method Detail

      • checkItemCollision

        public abstract void checkItemCollision(java.util.ArrayList<Item> mapItems)
        Signals that all subclasses must have this method so they can check if they have collided with any items on the map. This method can't exist here in the superclass, because Enemy and Player interact with Items slightly differently.
        Parameters:
        mapItems - The Items currently on the map, active or not.

      • processActiveItems

        public void processActiveItems(java.util.ArrayList<Item> mapItems)
                        throws org.newdawn.slick.SlickException
        When the very inner if statement is triggered, it means that the useEffect() method of the item in question returned true, indicating that its active effect on the player should end. As such, the Racer's modifiable movement variables, namely at this point the acceleration and angularModifier, are reset to the default and the item is removed from the Racer's active effects ArrayList.
        Parameters:
        mapItems - The items currently on the map. These need to passed through to the useEffect method so when the item is activated (e.g. a tomato is thrown), it can be added to the list of items currently on the map.
        Throws:
        org.newdawn.slick.SlickException
